702503668, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"emphatic style\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"the trio\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"47.738s\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"almost two seconds\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having proven his longevity in spade loads, Cundy noted that there are definitely a few more years left in him on the track ahead of a possible ninth Games in LA.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his longevity\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"spade loads\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"Cundy\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"a few more years\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"a possible ninth Games\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1192}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's hard to believe that I have got nine gold medals,\\\" said Cundy, who is one of over 1,000 elite athletes on UK Sport's National Lottery-funded World Class Programme, allowing them to train full time, have access to the world's best coaches and benefit from pioneering medical support - which has been vital on their pathway to the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nine gold medals\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"Cundy\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1,000 elite athletes\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's best coaches\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"medical support\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"their pathway\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Games\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could not have imagined where I'd be when I started this journey in 1996.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this journey\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Another gold medal around my neck and it's fabulous.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Another gold medal\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"my neck\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I love the sport and I am still able to compete at the top end and do the training that I need to.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"the top end\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"the training\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In November it will have been thirty years since I first represented Great Britian and I am still strong.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"November\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1801}, {\"ngram\": \"thirty years\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"Great Britian\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not sure I will be going another thirty years, but I can certainly get one or two more in there and then see where I am for LA.\\\"\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 2031, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't quite a world record for the trio - just shy of the one they set in Tokyo by 0.159s - but it wrapped up a glittering medal haul for ParalympicsGB in the velodrome as Britain soared to 14 medals, including five golds.\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2111, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999800385885987, \"rank\": 1.2048806154949132e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7237928965686399, \"rank\": 0.38161062786567007, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"quite a world record\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"the trio\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2076}, {\"ngram\": \"the one\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2098}, {\"ngram\": \"0.159s\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2126}, {\"ngram\": \"a glittering medal haul\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"ParalympicsGB\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"14 medals\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"five golds\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with enough gold medals to pick favourites, Cundy was already ranking the experience among one of the best he's had.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough gold medals\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"favourites\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"Cundy\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"the experience\", \"from\": 2335, \"to\": 2349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tokyo is still my favourite gold medal just because you never have the perfect race but that was,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999800385885987, \"rank\": 1.2048806154949132e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my favourite gold medal\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2422}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect race\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today we were not a million miles off that perfect race, but we had the crowd and friends and family here.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2600, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that perfect race\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2549}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"friends\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2583}, {\"ngram\": \"family\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's definitely high up there on my medals.\\\"\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2647, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my medals\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cox led off on the first lap in a storming 250m that put to bed any doubts she had after crashing out of the women's 500m time trial on the opening day of competition.\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cox\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2652}, {\"ngram\": \"the first lap\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"bed\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2712}, {\"ngram\": \"any doubts\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"500m\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening day\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With redemption coming in the form of a gold medal, Cox revealed that it tasted all the sweeter after a difficult start to the Games.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"redemption\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2868}, {\"ngram\": \"Cox\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2873}, {\"ngram\": \"a difficult start\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"After the highs and lows of this week it's nice to come out and win a Paralympic title,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the highs\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2969}, {\"ngram\": \"lows\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"this week\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"a Paralympic title\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd like to say it's frustrating to not have two but I am happy to have done what I needed to do for the boys.\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3165, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the boys\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It took a lot to get me back out here and I had to climb over a big hurdle to get back onto the start line.\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3181}, {\"ngram\": \"a big hurdle\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"the start line\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I tried not to tear up as I got out for the qualifiers as I was scared and did not want to disappoint the team or let myself down.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the qualifiers\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3332}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Being able to overcome that and go better in the final, I will give myself a pat on the pack.\\\"\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pat\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3491}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 3495, \"to\": 3503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James Ball and Sophie Unwin both topping the medal podium on a day that yielded three golds.\", \"from\": 3507, \"to\": 3599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Ball\", \"score\": 0.9999999950032361, \"rank\": 4.593676895123345e-09, \"text\": \"James Ball\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Ball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Ball\"}, {\"begin\": 3522, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Unwin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medal podium\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3564}, {\"ngram\": \"a day\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3573}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ball stormed to men's tandem kilo victory alongside pilot Steffan Lloyd and dethroned team-mate and Tokyo 2020 winner Neil Fachie in a time of 58.964s.\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3701, \"end\": 3706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999800385885987, \"rank\": 1.2048806154949132e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://db